# API consumption (Marham frontend)

All HTTP APIs live in **MarhamOne** (NestJS at `NEXT_PUBLIC_MARHAM_API_URL`). This Next.js project is a **consumer only**.

## Forbidden

- `app/api/**/route.ts` — Route Handlers
- Next.js API proxies or BFF layers
- Server Actions used as API endpoints
- TanStack `createServerFn` wrappers acting as backend logic
- Direct `fetch("/api/...")` to local Next.js routes

## Required workflow for new data needs

1. Implement endpoint in `MarhamOne/src/modules/` (controller → service → repository)
2. Update `MarhamOne/API_DOCUMENTATION.md`
3. Add typed fetch helper in `lib/` (e.g. `lib/marham-api.ts`)
4. Call helper from pages (Server Components) or components (Client Components)

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — Next.js API route
// app/api/doctors-listing/route.ts
export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  const data = await fetchDoctorsListing(...)
  return NextResponse.json(data)
}

// ❌ BAD — client calling local Next.js proxy
const res = await fetch("/api/doctors-listing?page=2")

// ✅ GOOD — lib helper calling MarhamOne (server or client)
import { fetchDoctorsListing } from "@/lib/marham-api"

// Server Component
const { doctors, meta } = await fetchDoctorsListing({ page: 1 }, { revalidate: 60 })

// Client Component
const { doctors, meta } = await fetchDoctorsListing({ page: currentPage + 1 })
```

## Env

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_MARHAM_API_URL` — NestJS base URL (e.g. `http://localhost:3000`)
- Never put secrets in `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` variables
